'''圣玛利亚堂'''（St Mary de Crypt Church）位于英格兰[[格洛斯特|格洛斯特]]南门街，是一座[[英格兰圣公会|英格兰圣公会]]<ref name=cny>[http://www.achurchnearyou.com/gloucester-st-mary-de-crypt/ St Mary de Crypt, Gloucester.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.achurchnearyou.com/gloucester-st-mary-de-crypt/ |date=20171002215230 }} A Church Near You, 2010. Retrieved 21 June 2011.</ref> [[教堂|教堂]]。它属于[[圣公会格洛斯特教区|圣公会格洛斯特教区]]，毗邻“灰衣修士修道院”（''Greyfriars''）遗址。它也称为"基督堂"和“南门圣玛利亚堂”。<ref name=glosgen>[http://www.glosgen.co.uk/gloucester/gloster2.htm St. Mary de Crypt Church.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.glosgen.co.uk/gloucester/gloster2.htm |date=20100513020330 }} City of Gloucester, Places of Worship, 2010. Retrieved 22 June 2011.</ref> 该堂是一座一级[[登录建筑|登录建筑]].<ref>{{NHLE|num=1245611 |desc=Church of St Mary de Crypt|accessdate=23 June 2011}}</ref>。

==历史==
圣玛利亚堂在1140年首次见于记载。自那时起在格洛斯特的历史中扮演了重要的角色。<ref name=visitglos/>

[[卫理公会|卫理公会]]的创始人之一[[乔治·怀特腓|乔治·怀特腓]]，于1736年第一次在该堂讲道<ref>Heighway, Carolyn. ''Gloucester: a history and guide.'' Gloucester: Alan Sutton Publishing Limited, 1985, p.141. {{ISBN|0-86299-256-7}}</ref> in 1736.<ref name=visitglos>[http://www.visit-gloucestershire.co.uk/gloucester/decrypt.htm St Mary de Crypt & Greyfriars.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.visit-gloucestershire.co.uk/gloucester/decrypt.htm |date=20110521032943 }} Gloucestershire Portal, 2006. Retrieved 23 June 2011.</ref>。

1952年，该教区与原圣米迦勒堂（St Michael's Church）合并<ref name=gct>[http://www.gloucestercivictrust.org.uk/gloucester-civic-trust/St-Michaels-Tower.html St Michael’s Tower at Gloucester Cross.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gloucestercivictrust.org.uk/gloucester-civic-trust/St-Michaels-Tower.html |date=20120328111804 }} [[Gloucester_Civic_Trust|Gloucester Civic Trust]], 2010. Retrieved 6 August 2011.</ref>。

2019年，经过两年的修复，已经年久失修的教堂得以重新开放，用于礼拜，以及创作、社区和活动中心。修复项目主要由国家彩票遗产基金136万欧元<ref name=guardian-20190324>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2019/mar/24/gloucester-church-with-literary-links-reopens-after-restoration-dickens |title=Gloucester church with literary 来自after £2.1m restoration |last=Morris |first=Steven |newspaper=The Guardian |date=24 March 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-date=2020-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215160920/https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2019/mar/24/gloucester-church-with-literary-links-reopens-after-restoration-dickens |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

